The paper deals with planar graphs and their embeddings, which are topics in computational geometry (cs.CG). The concept of nodal 3-connectivity is related to graph theory and connectivity algorithms (cs.DS). The paper also discusses weighted averages and characterizations of planar graphs, which are topics in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The use of convex combinations and embeddings suggests a connection to graph theory and topology (cs.GT). Finally, the paper may also be relevant to computational optimization and machine learning, as convex combinations are commonly used in these fields (cs.SI).
